 The ship loaded 659,133 bbls. (per B/L) at the MODEC Venture 1, Phillips'=20
floating offshore facility in Indonesia, from June 20-21.  Testing of the=20
shore tanks  at loading revealed that the Elang Crude did meet the=20
specifications in the FGPC contract.  ECT paid Phillips an FOB price of $20,=
=20
706,663.20 for the cargo. =20

 After loading in Indonesia, the ship then proceeded to Thailand, where from=
=20
June 28-30 it  off-loaded 410,697 bbls for storage, for the eventual use of=20
FGPC.  No quality testing of the product was apparently done aboard or ashor=
e=20
at that time.  The ship thereafter sailed to the Phillipines for off-loading=
=20
the remainder of the cargo.

 Upon off-loading in the Phillipines, the cargo was found off-spec for the=20
presence of metals and sediment.  FGPC rejected the cargo; Wilson, Farley=20
opined that FGPC was squarely within its contractual rights to do so.  ECT=20
